===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|waste|lang=enm}}, {{term|wast||stature, waist|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|*wǣst}}, {{term/t|ang|*wǣxt}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*wahstuz||growth, development, stature, build}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*aweks-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*auks-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*weks-||to multiply, increase}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|wahst||growth|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|vækst||growth|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|växt||growth, development, size|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|vöxtur||growth|lang=is}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|||tr=wahstus|growth|lang=got}}. Related to {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|weaxan||to grow, increase|lang=ang}}. More at {{l|en|wax}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/weɪst/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪst}}
* Homophones: [[waste]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[part]] of the [[body]] [[between]] the [[pelvis]] and the [[stomach]].
# A part of a [[piece]] of [[clothing]] that covers the waist.
# The [[narrow]] [[connection]] between the [[thorax]] and [[abdomen]] in certain [[insect]]s (e.g., [[bee]]s, [[ant]]s and [[wasp]]s).
# The middle portion of the [[hull]] of a [[ship]] or the [[fuselage]] of an [[aircraft]].
# {{context|nautical|lang=en}} That part of the upper deck of a ship between the [[quarterdeck]] and the [[forecastle]].
#*'''1851''', [[w:Herman Melville|Herman Melville]], ''[[w:Moby Dick|Moby Dick]]'', [[s:Moby-Dick/Chapter 18|chapter 18]]
#*:There he stood, very quietly overlooking some sailmakers who were mending a top-sail in the '''waist'''.
